spans.text: SON of the distant land , who dwellest in the secret cell !
to the masts : and the boisterous winds roared behind the groves of Morven
rocks , for the fall of the terrible Swaran
the sigh bursts from their breasts
Ma-ronnan , raise them to the winds of the west
OH Aldo , through the foam of the northern wave
us be renowned , OH Aldo , in the battles of echoing Sora
their swords and shields of thongs
to Sora's haughty king , the chief of bounding steeds
to Sora's haughty king , the chief of bounding steeds
the spouse of Erragon , the humid , rolling eyes of Lormar
of Erragon , the humid , rolling eyes of Lormar
young Aldo , like the beam of Sora's setting sun
ALDO of the heart of pride !
my tomb : my renown is in the song : and my actions shall be as a dream to future times
to pour them on the land of the stranger
or the land of many hills
Fingal , from thy hall , thou daughter of my love ; come from thy hall , Bosmina , maid of streamy Morven
bid the king of Sora to our feast
of Erragon , like a beam of light to a cloud
the feast of Morven's king , to Selma's shaded walls
once the kings of the world
that he spreads his feast in vain
Let Fingal pour his spoils around me
give me the swords of his fathers
the rising pride of the maid ; they are in the mighty hands of heroes who never yielded in war
the fall of thy people , son of the distant land
the fall of thy people , son of the distant land
he stretched his hand to his spear : — the ghosts of thousands were near
foresaw the death of the people
NOW the dogs of the chase
that his young heroes followed them
— then Morni's son , and Nemi's race : — Fercuth showed his gloomy form : Dermid spread his dark hair on the wind
the song of other times : my spear supported my steps over the little streams , and my thoughts were of mighty men
my steps over the little streams , and my thoughts were of mighty men
Three gray-haired sons of the song
like the shower of a storm when it pours on the narrow vale
hill : the sunbeam of battle flew on the wind
Fingal , like the bounding roe , like the heart of echoing Cona
with Erragon in the strife ! — Behold the battle of the chiefs
behold the face of the hill
his voice , loud and distant on the wind
thy echoing hills , hunter of woody Cona
her hero : her voice was heard no more : silent she rolled her sad eyes
no more : silent she rolled her sad eyes
